                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d44">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Denby</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-01-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 6, 1897</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1385.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your No.
                    2645, of November 24 last, inclosing copy of the note which, in compliance with
                    the Department’s instructions, you sent to the Tsung-li Yamên demanding the
                    punishment of officials who failed to do their duty in the protection of
                    American citizens at Kutien, and also damages for Miss Hartford.</p>
                <p>You will urge on the Yamên the necessity of prompt action.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
